    <hr align="center" width="90%" size="1" noshade color="#999999">
    <!-- article start -->
    <p><strong>CES Awards Programs: Go For The Gold! </strong><br> by Dan Cole</p>
    <p><P target="_blank"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">We are just 120 days away and counting! The 2009 International CES is just around the corner and after Labor Day, companies typically focus their full energy and efforts on ensuring the success of their show participation. </SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">If you’re like the rest of the world, you were most likely keeping an eye on the Olympics. My favorite part was watching the athletes who earn their spot on the medal stand. The pride these athletes feel and show is indescribable and inspiring at the same time. Whether an athlete is bringing home the gold, silver or bronze, those awards are the outward evidence of years of dedication, sacrifice and hard work. An achievement that brings positive recognition to both them and their country. </SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Are you aware that CES has several awards programs that can bring similar recognition to your company and its products or technologies? Whether you are a product designer or engineer, member of the press, or a maverick in the television and advanced media arena, CES has an award to recognize you.</SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Now in its 32<SUP>nd</SUP> year, the CES Innovations Design and Engineering Awards Program recognizes the pinnacle of innovation in the consumer electronics industry. With entrants from 34 different product categories representing the hottest technologies in the CE industry, the CES Innovations Awards have become the hallmark of the best designed products in consumer technology. <SPAN style="COLOR: black">The 2009 Best of Innovations honorees will be announced at the New York Press Preview on November 11, 2008, at the Metropolitan Pavilion and showcased at the 2009 International CES</SPAN>.</SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #3a3a3a; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">&nbsp;<A href="http://www.cesweb.org/awards/innovations/callForEntries.asp"><SPAN style="COLOR: #3e5aa6">Call for entries</SPAN></A> closes September 24. Make sure to visit to enter your product today.</SPAN></P>
