<a name="1705"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">Do You Know Who the Official CES Vendors Are?</div>
<br />

As a valued CES exhibitor, we wanted to take a moment to remind you of the official CES vendors, contractors and publications for the 2009 CES. </SPAN><BR><BR>The International CES has gone through a rigorous process of picking the right vendors and contractors for the show. Only the companies shown on the <A href="http://www.cesweb.org/docs/2009_CES_Official_Suppliers.pdf" target=_blank>list of official vendors and partners </A>&nbsp;are the official CES vendors; any claims to be official vendors by companies other than those listed are false.<BR><BR>While there are a number of publications out there covering the day-to-day events of the International CES, there are only a few "official" show publications that guide our attendees and exhibitors through their CES experience. These pieces include the <I>Preshow Planner, Show Guide, Show Directory, CES Show Daily</I>, <I>CES Mobile Today</I>, and <I>The</I> <I>Engineer's Guide to CES. </I><BR><BR>These publications offer prime advertising space for companies like yours to reach more that 130,000 qualified consumer technology professionals, including executives, decision-makers, buyers, distributors, engineers and a variety of other key audiences. Please visit our Sponsorship page for more information.<BR><BR>The best way to stay informed of all official communications it to download the CES Alert tool to your desktop. <A href="http://www.cesweb.org/exhibitors/newsletter/sep08.asp#1704" target=_blank>Read more information now.</A></SPAN><BR><BR>If you have any questions concerning our official CES vendors, partners and publications, please feel free to contact your sales representative for further clarification.
        <br /><img width="1" height="20" src="/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/images/framework/divider-line.gif"/><br />

<a name="1704"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">Now Available for Download - CES Alert – Stay Informed</div>
<br />

<IMG height=45 hspace=10 src="/images/content/CESalert.gif" width=100 align=right vspace=10>We are pleased to announce that “CES Alert” is now available to help with your preparation for the 2009 International CES. “CES Alert” is a personalized desktop tool that provides a secure communications channel from show management directly to you. You’ll receive important show information such as timely reminders of deadlines for show services. This is the second year we are using this tool. <A href="http://myces2009.bdmetrics.com/showspecificfiles/myces2009/GetExhibitorManager.html">Load the CES Alert on your system tray now.</A>
<P>If you have any questions, please contact customer support at 410-402-1028, option 1 or <A href="mailto:smartboothsupport@bdmetrics.com" target=_blank>smartboothsupport@bdmetrics.com</A>.</P>
        <br /><img width="1" height="20" src="/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/images/framework/divider-line.gif"/><br />

<a name="1703"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">Complete Your Free Exhibitor Directory Listing - Due October 17</div>
<br />

Attendees are already searching the 2009 International CES online exhibitor directory. <A href="https://myces.bdmetrics.com/exhibitorportal/eventlogin.aspx?ReturnUrl=%2fexhibitorportal%2fEDCWizard%2fWelcome.aspx" target=_blank>Complete your free CES exhibitor directory listing today</A>&nbsp;so they can find you! 
<P>For assistance with your directory listing, e-mail <A href="mailto:Support@BDMetrics.com" target=_blank>Support@BDMetrics.com</A> or call 800-931-5103 and select option 2. </P>
<P>Once you have completed your free directory listing you will have also activated your CES SmartBooth profile allowing you to take the next step to enhance your presence before, during and after the 2009 CES. Contact Gary Zgorski at <A href="mailto:gary.zgorski@bdmetrics.com" target=_blank>gary.zgorski@bdmetrics.com</A> for assistance with CES SmartBooth.</P>
<P>The deadline for your listing in the print <EM>Official International CES Show Directory</EM> is October 17, 2008.</P>
        <br /><img width="1" height="20" src="/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/images/framework/divider-line.gif"/><br />

<a name="1702"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">Please Join Us for a Complimentary Online Seminar – “Ensuring Success at the 2009 International CES Using Event-Centric Online Media.&quot; </div>
<br />

<IMG height=90 hspace=10 src="/images/content/myces.gif" width=150 align=right vspace=10>As the consumer electronics (CE) industry begins to focus and plan for the 2009 International CES in Las Vegas, <A href="/myCES.asp">MyCES</A> will become the industry’s top search engine and planning resource leading up to the show. Last year during the 10 weeks leading up to the show, over 1.4 million searches were conducted by attendees and industry professionals. Attendees use MyCES to plan their event, get a sneak peek at new products, and learn about other areas they can’t afford to miss at CES.<BR>During this brief presentation you will learn:<BR>
<UL class=text>
<LI class=text>How to get your corporate brand and new product information in front of your prospects up to 10 weeks before the show</LI>
<LI class=text>How to increase your visibility in the MyCES search engine</LI>
<LI class=text>How you can achieve (and report on) increased ROI at this year’s CES through web-based tools that extend the reach of your attendee marketing online </LI></UL><BR><A href="https://bdmetrics.webex.com/bdmetrics/onstage/g.php?t=a&d=687144386" target=_blank>Register now for the 2 p.m. September 10 webinar.</A> (Please note that space is limited.)<BR><BR>For questions, please call Tim Rader at 410-402-1056 or email <A href="mailto:tim.rader@bdmetrics.com" target=_blank>tim.rader@bdmetrics.com</A>
        <br /><img width="1" height="20" src="/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/images/framework/divider-line.gif"/><br />

<a name="1699"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">Visa Application Process</div>
<br />

With registration now open, it is time to begin the Visa application process. If you are an exhibitor that requires a Visa to enter the U.S., request your letter of invitation and make your appointment for a visa interview early. Wait times for a visa interview can be several weeks or more in many countries, especially during peak travel periods. With this in mind, we strongly urge you to register for CES and request a letter of invitation as soon as possible. <A href="/international/travel.asp">View helpful tips for securing your visa now.</A>
        <br /><img width="1" height="20" src="/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/images/framework/divider-line.gif"/><br />

<a name="1698"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">Exhibitor PR Newsletter</div>
<br />

The Exhibitor PR Newsletter is a monthly distribution designed to help you keep your public relations efforts in check with valuable tips, deadline reminders and breaking news. See the latest CES press events and discover ways to maximize your company’s media exposure all year long. By <A href="https://myces.bdmetrics.com/exhibitorportal/EventLogin.aspx" target=_blank>registering</A>, your PR contact will receive these important CES news tips on the first Wednesday of every month.<BR><BR><A href="/exhibitors/newsletter/7D5C8655161F4C6A81BE7E761FC6CFC1.htm">The newsletter will also be posted on CESweb.org</A> on the second Wednesday of the month, after all registered contacts have had the opportunity to receive it electronically.
        <br /><img width="1" height="20" src="/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/images/framework/divider-line.gif"/><br />

<a name="1697"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">Connect With the Press — Send Us Your PR Contact</div>
<br />

Leverage the CES PR tools and resources before, during and after the 2009 International CES by sending us your PR contact information.<BR><BR>To ensure that the media can find you at CES, please take a moment to list your company's PR contact. We will direct any media inquiries we receive regarding your company or products to the individual you indicate. The contact information will be available to all registered CES media. It is <I>required</I> that you go to your <A href="https://myces.bdmetrics.com/exhibitorportal/eventlogin.aspx?ReturnUrl=%2fexhibitorportal%2fEDCWizard%2fWelcome.aspx" target=_blank>free exhibitor directory listing profile</A> to add/update your PR contact information.<BR><BR>Questions? Contact Allison Carney at <A href="mailto:acarney@CE.org" target=_blank>acarney@CE.org</A>.
